@node "Motivation" "Motivation"
This one was written for all Amigians (like me), who want to know what is going on on
their machines. It shows infos about patches applied via patch.library to your system.

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS:

- Any Amiga with any Kickstart version
  (Kick V2.0+ is required for commandline options)
- patch.library v4+ must be installed in libs:
  (make sure you have the latest version)
@endnode


@node "Installation" "Installation"
'PatchList' can be placed anywhere you like. 
@endnode



@node "Notes" "Notes"
NOTES & WARNINGS & KNOWN BUGS:
@endnode



@node "Usage" "Usage"
The following commandline options are available for PatchList:
(Note: Kickstart V2.0+ is required for commandline options)

PROJECTS - Print patches sorted by projects

SHORT	 - Print a short overview of installed patches

FULL	 - Include printing of TaskLists

GLOBAL	 - Print global infos about patch.library (version, flags etc..)

DUMP	 - Print detailed debugging information including memory pointers,
	   internal flags, etc  (for debugging only)
@endnode



@node "Bugreports" "Bugreports"
If you find any bugs with PatchList please send me
a bugreport containing the following information:

- What versions of patch.library and PatchList (and PatchSetFunc) are you using?

- What exactly goes wrong?

- What must be done to reproduce the bug?

@endnode



@node "History" "History"

V2.3: FIX: Deadlock problem with new patch.library V6 Beta
      ENHANCEMENT: Recompiled with SAS/C V6.58

Most important changes since the V1.x versions:
- PatchList now knows about new features introduced with patch.library
  V3 and V4: (Projects, TaskLists, ....)
- If the FD: assignment is found the name of the patched function, instead
  of the LVO, is given.
- You can press CTRL-C to abort PatchList
- The source is no longer available, as PatchList now uses lots of
  patch.library private stuff
@endnode



